# Line-ending policy. Windows contributors typically run with core.autocrlf=true,
# which would otherwise check these files out with CRLF and break tooling:
#   *.patch — `git apply` rejects CRLF patches ("corrupt patch at <file>:N" on an
#             empty context line whose lone \r is not a valid diff prefix).
#   *.sh    — bash (Git Bash on Windows) mis-parses CRLF scripts ("\r command
#             not found", shebang breakage).
# Pin them to LF regardless of the machine's autocrlf setting.
*.patch text eol=lf
*.sh    text eol=lf
